---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const breadcrumb = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
  '@id': 'https://geoiplocations.com/platform.html#breadcrumb',
  itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://geoiplocations.com/' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Platform', item: 'https://geoiplocations.com/platform.html' },
  ],
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title="GeoIP Platform Overview, Coverage, ASN and Registry Intelligence | ProdIPData"
  description="Explore the ProdIPData platform for GeoIP coverage, ASN intelligence, registry context, and monthly publication workflows."
  ogTitle="GeoIP Platform Overview, Coverage, ASN and Registry Intelligence"
  canonicalPath="/platform.html"
  page="platform"
>
  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" is:inline set:html={JSON.stringify(breadcrumb)} />

  <main>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="page-panel glass">
          <div class="eyebrow page-kicker">Platform</div>
          <h1>GeoIP data built for practical use.</h1>
          <p class="page-intro">
            GeoIP Locations is the public data experience of ProdIPData. It helps teams explore country coverage, ASN structure,
            registry footprint, and downloadable files that can be used in analytics, routing, applications, and operational workflows.
          </p>
          <p class="page-intro seo-links">Explore the <a href="coverage.html">interactive country coverage map</a>, open the <a href="downloads.html">monthly GeoIP download indexes</a>, browse the <a href="releases/index.html">release archive</a>, open the <a href="releases/2026-04/index.html">current release overview</a>, or review the <a href="methodology.html">ProdIPData methodology</a> to understand how each release is assembled.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container grid-3">
        <article class="section-card glass">
          <h3>Downloadable GeoIP data</h3>
          <p class="card-text">Country profiles, ASN views, registry summaries, and downloadable file catalogs are published in formats that fit local analysis, reporting, and system integration.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="section-card glass">
          <h3>Reliable static delivery</h3>
          <p class="card-text">The public website is intentionally static. That keeps access simple, reduces operational risk, and lets teams review the published data without depending on a live production database.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="section-card glass">
          <h3>Monthly refresh cycle</h3>
          <p class="card-text">The platform is refreshed on a monthly cadence so users can work from a consistent release snapshot across the website, downloadable files, and supporting reference material.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-head">
          <div><h2>Find the right starting point</h2></div>
          <p>
            These guide pages target the most common discovery intents for a GeoIP data website and connect directly to the live ProdIPData surfaces.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="download-grid">
          <article class="section-card glass"><h3><a href="geoip-database.html">GeoIP database downloads</a></h3><p class="card-text">Product-oriented overview of downloadable GeoIP files, local hosting, and monthly releases.</p></article>
          <article class="section-card glass"><h3><a href="ip-geolocation-data.html">IP geolocation data</a></h3><p class="card-text">Plain-language guide to what GeoIP data represents and how to interpret it responsibly.</p></article>
          <article class="section-card glass"><h3><a href="asn-data-by-country.html">ASN data by country</a></h3><p class="card-text">Country-level operator structure, concentration, and lead-network context.</p></article>
          <article class="section-card glass"><h3><a href="geoip-csv-download.html">GeoIP CSV downloads</a></h3><p class="card-text">CSV-first guide for SQL, spreadsheets, and operational workflows.</p></article>
          <article class="section-card glass"><h3><a href="geoip-parquet-download.html">GeoIP Parquet downloads</a></h3><p class="card-text">Parquet-first guide for analytics and larger-scale processing paths.</p></article>
          <article class="section-card glass"><h3><a href="releases/index.html">GeoIP monthly release archive</a></h3><p class="card-text">Release-centric entry point for month-by-month navigation, current release context, and package-level paths.</p></article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container story-grid">
        <div class="split-panel glass content">
          <h2>What the platform supports</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Country-by-country coverage views and global summaries that help users understand where published internet footprint is concentrated.</li>
            <li>ASN and registry insights that make it easier to review network ownership, leading operators, and market structure.</li>
            <li>Downloadable CSV, Parquet, and MMDB files that can be hosted locally and integrated into internal tools, analytics flows, and data pipelines.</li>
            <li>Browser-based tables, charts, and maps that help teams compare countries, registries, and network composition without extra tooling.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container story-grid">
        <div class="split-panel glass content">
          <h2>ProdIPData files</h2>
          <p>
            ProdIPData files are designed for teams that want to download GeoIP data, host it locally, and integrate it into their own
            reporting, applications, or operational workflows. Monthly CSV, Parquet, and MMDB packages make it easier to move from website
            exploration to direct internal use.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Access monthly release files through dedicated HTML package indexes.</li>
            <li>Review metadata such as snapshot month, package structure, and published footprint counts.</li>
            <li>Use files for internal analytics, routing reviews, enrichment jobs, and downstream data preparation.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="split-panel glass content">
          <h2>Beyond geolocation</h2>
          <p>
            GeoIP is not only about approximate location. ProdIPData extends the picture with ASN, registry, and market-structure views
            so users can understand who operates the visible footprint, how concentrated a country may be, and how coverage is distributed.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Country and registry views help explain overall scale and regional distribution.</li>
            <li>ASN panels and rankings provide operator context beyond simple location labels.</li>
            <li>Concentration and composition views support more informed interpretation of the published internet footprint.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" data-wave4-block="discovery-links">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="split-panel glass content">
          <h2>Explore deeper release and entity pages</h2>
          <p>
            The monthly release archive connects the current dataset to focused country, registry, and ASN pages. Use the <a href="releases/index.html">monthly release archive</a> for time-based navigation, open <a href="country/index.html">country profiles</a> for country-level footprint context, review <a href="rir/index.html">RIR pages</a> for registry-level coverage, and open <a href="asn/index.html">ASN profiles</a> for visible network entities in the current release. For package access, continue through <a href="downloads.html">GeoIP CSV, Parquet, and MMDB downloads</a>, and for source quality and caveats, review <a href="methodology.html">GeoIP methodology and validation</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
